<subSubSection id="F8FE6550413BFFD8FF44620D9B6C3EA2" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="B05B36DB413BFFD8FF44620D9B6C3EA2" blockId="6.[151,1437,1378,1984]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis id="8290EAC9413BFFD8FF44620D9B703E10" bold="true" box="[197,341,1880,1906]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Discussion.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="77E44D58413BFFD8FEDC620C9BCA3E10" box="[349,495,1881,1906]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fastigata">
<emphasis id="8290EAC9413BFFD8FEDC620C9BCA3E10" box="[349,495,1881,1906]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">D. fastigata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the only spoon tarsus species endemic to O‘ahu. Due to its morphological similarity to 
<taxonomicName id="77E44D58413BFFD8FEB062D59BD93EFB" box="[305,508,1920,1945]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atroscutellata">
<emphasis id="8290EAC9413BFFD8FEB062D59BD93EFB" box="[305,508,1920,1945]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">D. atroscutellata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, this species is included in this group, but is also considered basal due to the reduced spoon.
</paragraph>
